<title>UK: Bass off as HSBC rates it a &quot;sell&quot;.</title>
<headline>Bass off as HSBC rates it a &quot;sell&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Bass Plc slipped on Monday after analysts at HSBC changed its recommendation for the brewery-to-hotels group from &quot;hold&quot; to &quot;sell&quot;.</p>
<p>By 1130 GMT Bass were down 5p at 749p.</p>
<p>&quot;Basically we do not see where the growth will come from,&quot; Charles Winston at HSBC said.</p>
<p>He would not give any further details at moment, he said.</p>
